Azure CLI Interactive Mode is a feature that provides an enhanced command-line experience with auto-completion, command suggestions, and real-time help. It simplifies the learning curve for beginners and improves productivity for experienced users.

Users can enter interactive mode by running the command: az interactive

In this mode, users receive suggestions for commands and parameters, reducing the chances of syntax errors.

For example, a beginner who is unsure about the exact syntax for creating a virtual machine can use interactive mode to explore commands step by step.

A real-life use case includes training environments where new team members are learning Azure CLI. Interactive mode helps them understand available commands without constantly referring to documentation.

Another example is troubleshooting. Engineers can quickly explore commands and test configurations in real-time without writing full scripts.

This feature bridges the gap between GUI-based usage and full command-line expertise.
